  <title>acid anhydrides</title>
  <termversion>2.3.3</termversion>
  <lastupdated>2014-02-24</lastupdated>
  <definitions>
    <item>
      <id>1</id>
      <text>Compounds consisting of two acyl groups bonded to the same oxygen atom acyl-O-acyl. Symmetric and mixed anhydrides have identical and different acyl groups, respectively. E.g. [image: Not defined]acetic anhydride, [image: Not defined] acetic benzenesulfonic anhydride, [image: Not defined] (thiobenzoic) anhydride.</text>
